  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a DCF model for Motorola Solutions?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">A Discounted Cash Flow model determines the absolute intrinsic value of a business by projecting its future cash-generating ability, rather than relative valuation multiples which only show market sentiment.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How sensitive is this to the discount rate?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Very sensitive. A lower discount rate implies a lower required rate of return and will drastically inflate the intrinsic value. Refer to the sensitivity matrix for a broader view.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why is Free Cash Flow so important?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Free Cash Flow is the true measure of a company's financial flexibility. It is the cash remaining after all operational and capital expenses have been paid, which can be used to pay dividends, reduce debt, or reinvest in growth.</div>
